definitions.definition: A person who carries luggage and related objects.
examples: By the time I reached the train station I was exhausted, but fortunately there was a porter waiting.

definitions.definition: ( entomology ) An ant having the specialized role of carrying .
( computing ) One who ports software ( makes it usable on another platform ) .

main_definition: A person who carries luggage and related objects.
secondary_definitions: ( entomology ) An ant having the specialized role of carrying .
( computing ) One who ports software ( makes it usable on another platform ) .

definitions.definition: A person in control of the entrance to a building.
An employee who clears and cleans tables and puts bowling balls away.
A strong, dark ale , originally favored by porters (etymology 1, sense 1), similar to a stout but less strong.

main_definition: ( countable ) A person in control of the entrance to a building.
secondary_definitions: ( countable , bowling ) An employee who clears and cleans tables and puts bowling balls away.
( countable , uncountable , beer ) A strong, dark ale , originally favored by porters (etymology 1, sense 1), similar to a stout but less strong.
